  "prompt": "How does magnesium oxide react with water?",
  "response": "Magnesium oxide (MgO) reacts with water (H2O) to form magnesium hydroxide (Mg(OH)2). The reaction can be represented by the following chemical equation:\n\n\\[ \\text{MgO} + \\text{H}_2\\text{O} \\rightarrow \\text{Mg(OH)}_2 \\]\n\nThis is an exothermic reaction, meaning it releases heat. Magnesium hydroxide is a weak base and is sparingly soluble in water. The reaction typically occurs slowly at room temperature, but it can be accelerated by heating the mixture.",
